<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p class="p1"><strong>The dramatic untamed wilderness of the Canadian Rocky Mountains is one of the ‘must-see’ natural wonders of the world. </strong></p>
<p class="p1">Our leisurely tour gives you time to enjoy all 3 resorts to the full, starting with 5 nights in magnificent Lake Louise, with its excellent walking trails and the sublime beauty of Moraine Lake and nearby Yoho National Park. Next we drive the spellbinding 230 km Icefields Parkway with its lofty peaks, giant glaciers and aquamarine lakes to Jasper. Here we enjoy 4 nights in this friendly little frontier town with time to explore the legendary beauty of Maligne Lake and the wide range of activities, excursions, walking and wildlife in the Rockies’ largest national park. Our final 5 nights are spent in the lively town of Banff with its stunning setting, wealth of shops, bars, restaurants, guided excursions and outdoor pursuits. In each resort our Inghams representative will be on hand to recommend how best to enjoy your holiday to the full.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Itinerary</h2>
<p><strong>4 NIGHTS, LAKE LOUISE</strong> Fly to Calgary and transfer to magnificent Lake Louise in Banff National Park. In addition to the many scenic walks from Lake Louise and sublime Moraine Lake, take an excursion to Yoho National Park, Takakkaw Falls and Emerald Lake, raft the Kicking Horse River, visit a grizzly bear refuge, go horse riding or canoeing or take the mountain gondola.<br /><strong>5 NIGHTS, JASPER</strong> Start with an absolutely spellbinding 230km trip along the Icefields Parkway, one of the world’s great drives, stopping at Peyto Lake and Athabasca-Falls en route. In friendly Jasper there are endless excursions, recreational and walking opportunities. Don’t miss a cruise to Spirit Island on lovely Maligne Lake,<br />white-water rafting or a walk to Angel Glacier at Cavell Meadows.<br /><strong>5 NIGHTS, BANFF</strong> After retracing our steps along the Icefields Parkway, stopping at the Columbia Icefields<br />for an optional tour, we arrive in the lively town of Banff with its many shops, restaurants and excursion possibilities. Highlights include Lake Minnewanka, Johnston Canyon, the gondola and hot springs, and a visit to the famous Banff Springs Hotel.</p>
<p><strong>JASPER ITINERARY VARIATIONS</strong><br />Your last 2 night stay in Jasper can be changed to a 2 day Back-country Hiking Experience at Glacier Lake. Call reservations on 01483 79 11 11 for details.</p>
<p><strong>BANFF ITINERARY VARIATIONS</strong><br />The last 2 nights in Banff can be changed to a 2 day Guest Ranch Stay &amp; Horseback Ride or 2 day Heli-camping in Kananaskis Country. Call reservations on 01483 79 11 11 for details.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Inghams Plus</h2>
<p><strong>EARLY BOOKING OFFER SAVE up to £130</strong> per couple (book by 31 Mar 2014).<br />This discount has automatically been included in the price shown.<br /><strong>FREE</strong> gondola ride up Mount Whitehorn in Lake Louise<br /><strong>FREE</strong> bicycle hire in Jasper<br /><strong>FREE</strong> helicopter sightseeing flight in Banff<br /><strong>SAVE £250 PER COUPLE ON FREE EXCURSIONS</strong></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>What’s included</h2>
<p>Return flights from the UK to Calgary.<br />• Scenic coach transfers between each resort and to/from Calgary airport<br />• Hotel rooms all with private bath or shower. The Deluxe room supplement in 5 star hotels (see price panel) includes a Fairmont room with lake view in Lake Louise, a Junior Suite with lake view in Jasper and a Fairmont room with valley view in Banff<br />• Hotel meals Deluxe hot and cold breakfast is included for 5 star Fairmont hotels only. Breakfasts at 3 and 4 star hotels are payable locally<br />• Inghams Representatives in each resort</p>
<p> </p>
<p>All suggestions and excursions are bookable with our Representative and paid locally. Please note that we act at all times as selling agent for the suppliers of activities &amp; excursions.</p>
<div style="columns: 100px 2; -webkit-columns: 100px 2; /* safari and chrome */-moz-columns: 100px 2;"></div>
</div>
<div> </div>
